lScope> </bibl> </cit>: later, generally, <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">strong, powerful</tr_>, <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">ἰφθίμης φιλότητος</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0084.tlg001:655\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ D.P.\">D.P.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">655</biblScope> </bibl> </cit>:—<bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Hom.</author> </bibl> uses <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ἰφθίμη</foreign> of women; but <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ἴφθιμοι ψυχαί, κεφαλαί</foreign>, speaking of men. (No <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ϝ-</foreign>; prob. not cogn. with <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ἴς, ἶφι</foreign>.)</sense> </entryFree>"}]}